            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In n(omine) D(omi)ni. Constat me <persName key="#Deacons #Abbots #Monks"
                            ref="#people/1554">Andreas</persName> gr(aci)a D(e)i <rs key="#Deacons"
                            >diacon(us)</rs> et <rs key="#Monks">monachus</rs> adq(ue) <rs
                            key="#Abbots">abb(as)</rs> regula <rs key="#Monasteries"
                            >mon(asterii)</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Monasteries #Deacons #Abbots #Monks"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1487">S(an)c(t)i A[polen]a[ri]s q(ui) voc(atur)
                            Nov[o]</orgName> accepisse(m) et [a]ccepit a vob(is) <persName><name
                                ref="Apollinaris">Apolema[r]is</name></persName> filio q(uon)d(am)
                                <persName><name ref="Iohannes">Ioh(anni)s</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Rent_in_money">pensione</rs>
                        <rs key="#Landed_possessions">p(ro) tres uncias int(e)g(ras)</rs> q(ui)
                        e(st) posita in [<rs key="#Fundi">fundu(m)</rs>] q(ui) voc(atur) <geogName
                            key="#Fundi #Landed_possessions #Rent_in_money" ref="#estates/2421"
                                ><placeName key="#Fundi #Landed_possessions #Rent_in_money"
                                >Colopedio</placeName></geogName> cu(m) om(n)ib(us) sibi
                        p(er)tinentib(us), <rs key="#Fines">territorio</rs>
                        <geogName key="#Fines" ref="#estates/2422"><placeName key="#Fines"
                                ref="#places/3515">Liviense</placeName></geogName>, <rs key="#Plebs"
                            >plebe</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Plebs" ref="#juridical_persons/1488">S(an)c(t)e
                            Reparate</orgName>, quas p(er) <rs key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis"
                            >e[nfiteusin]</rs> tenere viso estis ad iure mon(asteri)i n(ost)ri, et
                        p(er) una(m)qua(m)q(ue) indic(ione) <rs key="#Rent_in_money">denarii
                            q(ui)nq(ue) tantu(m)</rs>. Unde p(ro) [munimine] vestro fec(it) vob(is)
                        hoc deaccepto in m(en)se mar(cio), indic(ione) X, <placeName
                            ref="#places/594">Rav(enne)</placeName>. Andreas diac(onus) et abb(as)
                        mon(asterii) S(an)c(t)i Apolinaris in oc deacepto s(ub)s(cripsi).</ab>
